Here's an HTML and JavaScript code for a calculator that computes the average value of `d = max(floor(i) * (b-a) + a, 0)` for `i` ranging from 0 to 99:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Average Calculator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        .calculator {
            background-color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        input[type="number"] {
            width: 50px;
            padding: 5px;
            margin-right: 10px;
        }
        input[type="button"] {
            padding: 5px 10px;
        }
        #result {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-left: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="calculator">
        <input type="number" id="a" placeholder="a">
        <span> and </span>
        <input type="number" id="b" placeholder="b">
        <input type="button" value="Calculate Average" onclick="calculateAverage()">
        <span id="result"></span>
    </div>

    <script>
        function calculateAverage() {
            var a = parseFloat(document.getElementById('a').value);
            var b = parseFloat(document.getElementById('b').value);
            if (a > b) {
                document.getElementById('result').textContent = "Error: 'a' should be less than 'b'";
                return;
            }
            
            var sum = 0;
            for (var i = 0; i <= 99; i++) {
                var d = Math.max(Math.floor(i) * (b - a) + a, 0);
                sum += d;
            }

            var average = sum / 100;
            document.getElementById('result').textContent = average.toFixed(2);
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **HTML**: This code includes two input fields for numbers `a` and `b`, a button to calculate the average, and a `span` to display the result.
- **CSS**: Simple styling is applied to center the calculator and give it a clean look.
- **JavaScript**: The `calculateAverage` function:
  - Validates that `a` is less than `b`.
  - Loops through values of `i` from 0 to 99.
  - For each `i`, it calculates `d = max(floor(i) * (b - a) + a, 0)`.
  - Sums all the values of `d` and then calculates the average.
  - Displays the average with two decimal places.

This code will calculate the desired average and display it when you press the "Calculate Average" button.
